title: For Sale:  RE: free add = overpriced guns
postcontent:
http://www.armslist.com/posts/3015327/denver-colorado-handguns-for-sale--free-add---overpriced-guns

 yeap, I totally agree, prices for used and new guns posted in Denver-Armslist are WAY overpriced.  If you are a seller, don't you think the buyer can look up the same gun from other vendors, other states, other on-line stores, other discount gun stores, pawn shops, etc?  It is true, you pay nothing for the add so you figure, "oh shoot, I'll just overprice it and see who takes the bait' or "I paid this much so is worth that much".  Well, no replies to your add, NO PHONE CALLS OR what you call "low baller" is what you get when you overprice your stuff.
Wanna sell? price accordingly, just because is a free add does not mean you can ask whatever you want and it will be ok. it's not. makes you look greedy and out of touch with what the market can bear as the OP said.

As for the FFL'ers charging more than $10 for person to person transfers (some greedy bastards want 30-40-50 bucks), they are CROOKS and are taking advantage of YOU.  See NRA synopsis for CO gun laws. It states specifically transfer fee is $10  !

http://www.nraila.org/gun-laws/state-laws/colorado.aspx

Buyers of shooting guns (not collectors), educate yourselves.  Sellers, be reasonable on your asking price, specially if it is used stuff.  One round fired from that gun after the test shot, it is in used condition and depreciated some 25% already! just like your car, your fridge, stereo, etc.

At least we can buy it if someone has it listed on here and it isn't to far away to drive to get it. I never saw that much ammo on the shelves anyways. If you really talk with the sporting goods stores and stores like Walmart, BiMart and Fred Meyers that sell it they tell me they don't get that much in anyways. Everything in America we buy was bought by someone before us. It is all part of the wholesale/retail and supply/demand game we all live by. These people that call these sellers scalpers obviously are very honest people and would never resell something at a profit. What a DUMBASS each one of them must be to not understand that is how the U.S.A. economy works. Let's try something. Sell me your house for less than what you paid for it. Better yet, sell me your 401 retirement package for half of what you have invested in it. 
SORRY I GOT SIDETRACKED. For Mother's Day weekend with the wife and adult sons we need at least 1 box of 500 or more rounds of 22LR. 10 cents a round is fines. Also need 44 Magnum ammo and 45 Long Colt. Since I bought a Circuit Judge 3 years ago I have had a hard time getting the 45 Long Colts for it. I don't like shooting the 410 slugs because they aren't very accurate at distance.
